==========================================================================================
Section 1 : Information regarding the tbb-malloc-matmat-split directory structure.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README          - Gives quick information regarding Package and how to execute
include/       --> consists of header files
src/           --> contains source file and main file.

                   the code.

=============================================================================================
Section 2 : Steps for using tbb-malloc-matmat-split] 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copy the " tbb-malloc-matmat-split.tar". Untar the file using
         $tar -xvf   tbb-malloc-matmat-split


in your home directory. This will create folder " tbb-malloc-matmat-split"

The following directory structure of  TBB-MAT-VECT-MALLOC  will be created in the
main directory i.e " tbb-malloc-matmat-split".

          /include        /src          


==============================================================================================
Section 3 : Pre-Requisites.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TBB2.0 should be installed and configured with Linux /Unix OS.

===============================================================================================
Section 4 : Steps for compiling   tbb-malloc-matmat-split
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Go in the respective directory(src)
and give
         make


===============================================================================================
Section 5 : Steps for executing  tbb-malloc-matmat-split
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


	./name_of_executable  size  Number-of-threads




